stinguish between the words only by their prior probabilities­ this follows from the way the method calculates sentence probabilities. [CLS] [SEP] Thus, for {between, among}, for example, where both words are prepositions, trigrams score the same as the baseline method. [CLS] [SEP] In such cases, the Bayesian hybrid method is clearly better. [CLS] [SEP] On the other hand, when the words in the confusion set have different parts of speech- as in, for example, {there, their, they're}­ trigrams are often better than the Bayesian method. [CLS] [SEP] We believe this is because trigrams look not just at a few words on either side of the target word, but at the part-of-speech sequence of the whole sentence. [CLS] [SEP] This analysis indicates a complementarity between trigrams and Bayes, and suggests a 52 combination in which trigrams would be applied first, but if trigrams determine that the words in the confusion set have the same part of speech for the sentence at issue, then the sentence would be passed to the Bayesian method. [CLS] [SEP] This is a research direction we plan to pursue. [CLS] [SEP] The work reported here builds on Yarowsky's use of decision lists to combine two component methods- context words and collocations. [CLS] [SEP] Decision lists pool the evidence from the two methods, and solve a target problem by applying the single strongest piece of evidence, whichever type that happens to be. [CLS] [SEP] This paper investigated the hypothesis that even better performance can be obtained by basing decisions on not just the single strongest piece of evidence, but on all available evidence. [CLS] [SEP] A method for doing this, based on Bayesian classifiers, was presented. [CLS] [SEP] It was applied to the task of context-sensitive spelling correction, and was found to outperform the component methods as well as decision lists. [CLS] [SEP] A comparison of the Bayesian hybrid method with Schabes's trigram-based method suggested a further combination in which trigrams would be used when the words in the confusion set had different parts of speech, and the Bayesian method would be used otherwise. [CLS] [SEP] This is a direction we plan to pursue in future research.